MSPs have backed Kenny MacAskill as Justice Secretary after he faced calls at Holyrood to step down. Justice Secretary survives calls to remove him MSPs have backed Kenny MacAskill as Justice Secretary after he faced calls at Holyrood to step down.A Labour-led attack on Mr MacAskill's position over his handling of controversial police and court reform was defeated by the SNP's slim majority at the Scottish Parliament.Labour MSP Graeme Pearson, who lodged the motion urging the Justice Secretary to resign, claimed Mr MacAskill had failed to provide effective governance of Police Scotland during a series of recent controversies. 